    <item>
      <title>为什么共和党仍在绘制众议院地图，而民主党则陷入困境</title>
      <link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/11/us/politics/redistricting-republicans-democrats.html</link>
      <description><![CDATA[共和党得益于两项法院裁决，该党在选区重新划分方面占据了优势，并且在中期选举前有更多的回旋空间来争取额外席位。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/11/us/politics/redistricting-republicans-democrats.html</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 01:51:32 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>领导关闭美国之音的卡里·莱克被任命为驻牙买加大使</title>
      <link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/11/us/politics/kari-lake-jamaica-ambassador.html</link>
      <description><![CDATA[莱克女士曾尝试解雇数百名美国之音记者，并削减自由欧洲电台/自由电台等其他联邦政府资助的新闻团体的资金，但均以失败告终。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/11/us/politics/kari-lake-jamaica-ambassador.html</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 01:06:11 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>最高法院为阿拉巴马州使用新投票地图扫清道路</title>
      <link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/11/us/politics/supreme-court-alabama-map.html</link>
      <description><![CDATA[大多数法官支持阿拉巴马州，此举可能会加快制定国会选区地图的努力，以消除黑人占多数的选区。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/11/us/politics/supreme-court-alabama-map.html</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 00:33:02 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>弗吉尼亚州官员要求最高法院恢复民主党绘制的投票地图</title>
      <link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/11/us/politics/supreme-court-virginia-redistricting.html</link>
      <description><![CDATA[州官员要求法官推翻弗吉尼亚州最高法院的一项裁决，该裁决推翻了国会地图，这是民主党的重大失败。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/11/us/politics/supreme-court-virginia-redistricting.html</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 11 May 2026 23:59:19 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
